From e5111ab9f8c9657a7bdd4c8c1dba588c24c20446 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 15:31:28 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C fix: bump data provider after setViewModel + restore
 Comments view
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The setCommentsForPr / registerDiffUri logs appeared but no
getDocumentComments fired and no native comment widgets appeared.
Two compounding issues:

1. **Editor `editor.contrib.review` is `AfterFirstRender`** —
   instantiated up to ~50ms after the inner editor's model attaches.
   Our controller registers eagerly at singleton init, well before
   any KRT diff editor exists. The `onDidSetDataProvider` event we
   fire then has no listeners; subsequent `onDidSetResourceComment-
   Infos` and `onDidUpdateCommentThreads` fall on the same gap. By
   the time the editor's CommentController instantiates, the events
   it relies on for its initial compute are gone, so it never queries
   our `getDocumentComments`.

   Fix: `bumpDataProvider()` on the controller — unregister + re-
   register, which re-fires `onDidSetDataProvider`.
   `KrtPrMultiDiff.setPullRequest` schedules a bump 150ms after
   `setViewModel`, comfortably past the `AfterFirstRender` 50ms
   idle-timeout. The newly-listening editors trigger their initial
   compute and pick up the threads we already published.

2. **Comments view (bottom panel) was missing** — Phase A's strip
   removed `krtCommentsView.contribution.ts`, which Phase 9.5 had
   added because upstream's `MainThreadComments` only registers the
   Comments view when an extension declares the `comments`
   contribution. KRT has no such extension, so without this we
   register the view ourselves. Restored as `hideIfEmpty: true` —
   appears once `setWorkspaceComments` publishes a non-empty thread
   set.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
